$ %appdata%\Microsoft\Excel\XLSTART

The *XLSTART directory* is the directory where → Microsoft/Office/Excel[Excel] searches for workbook templates and the 
→ Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Microsoft/Excel/XLSTART/Personal_xlsb[`Personal.xlsb`] file.

The special (→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Templates[template]) files (`.xltx`, `.xltm`) `Book.xlt*` and `Sheet.xlt*` are used as defaults when a new Excel workbook or worksheet is created.

Additionally, Excel opens all files that it finds in the XLSTART file.

{ Finding the XLSTART directory

  The default location for XLSTART is `%appdata%\Microsoft\Excel\XLSTART`.

  If this directory is not found under the default location, it might be found by executing (querying really) → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application/startupPath[`application.startupPath`] in
  the → Microsoft/Office/Visual-Basic-Editor/Immediate-Window[immediate window].

}
sa:
  The `AltStartup` value under the → Windows/registry[registry] key
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Excel/Options#reg-excel-alt-startup[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\_version_\Excel\Options`].

